    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-03-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-03-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="763"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d763">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/3–2453</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                            State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d763fn1">Drafted by Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                            >Dulles</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-03-24">March 24,
                            1953</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kashmir</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Kashmir situation is becoming increasingly acute and war between India and
                    Pakistan is a not remote possibility. The UN effort has bogged down. Would you
                    think that <persName corresp="#p_HPG1">Paul Hoffman</persName> might go on a
                    private mission to explore confidentially the attitude of the two parties to
                    some partition of Kashmir? It would seem that such a project might be acceptable
                    and it is the only solution which now seems to have practicable
                    possibilities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">John Foster Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
